&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To answer this question, we need to understand that, in a cultural sense, a mother is the one who gives birth to a child; therefore, the child comes later than the mother. Keeping that in mind, Hindi is the daughter of many North Indian languages. Let&amp;rsquo;s explore that a little further.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
